{"user_message": {"title": "ADR 0009 + Scoped Task — `roundToCents` half-up money primitive (1 task, 2 pts)", "content": "## ADR 0009 — Promote `roundToCents` to a named primitive in the money kernel\n\n**Status:** Accepted (2026-06-02) · Extends ADR 0002 (banker's rounding), ADR 0005 (money kernel consolidation)\n\n### Context\nThe seed asks for a tiny, well-tested pure `roundToCents(amount: number): number` (half-up, 2 dp) under the ledger/money-utilities area. Grounding in the codebase first: this rule **already exists privately** — an unexported `Math.round((n + Number.EPSILON) * 100) / 100` helper inside `src/features/ledger/lib/amount.ts` (used by `parseAmount`/`isValidSignedAmount`), with **no direct test of its own**. The canonical home for cross-cutting money primitives is the shared kernel `src/lib/money` (ADR 0005), which already exports `roundMoney` (currency-aware **half-EVEN**, ADR 0002), `addMoney`/`subtractMoney`, and `formatMoney`.\n\n### Decision\nAdd a **new focused file** `src/lib/money/round-to-cents.ts` exporting a named `roundToCents(amount: number): number` that canonicalizes a USD-cents value to 2 dp using **half-UP** (`Math.round((amount + Number.EPSILON) * 100) / 100` — behavioral parity with the existing private helper). Barrel-export it from `src/lib/money/index.ts`. Co-locate a unit test. This is a clean promote-and-test increment: one named, importable, tested primitive instead of a third private copy.\n\n**Why half-UP here and NOT `roundMoney`'s half-EVEN:** these are intentionally distinct. `roundMoney` is half-even to avoid upward bias when *summing many rows* (aggregates). `roundToCents` is the input-boundary canonicalizer (half-up) matching `amount.ts`'s existing contract. The ADR must spell this out so they are never conflated.\n\n### Consequences\n- New public primitive `@/lib/money` → `roundToCents`; first direct test coverage of the half-up rule.\n- **Explicitly OUT OF SCOPE this increment** (do NOT touch): `src/features/ledger/lib/amount.ts` (hot file in the parallel, delivery-stranded amount-validation increment — editing it risks a collision); `round.ts`/`arithmetic.ts`/`format.ts`; any route or feature code. De-duplicating `amount.ts` to import the new util is logged as separate future-work, NOT bundled here.\n\n---\n\n## Task breakdown (1 task · 2 story points)\n\n### T1 — Add `roundToCents` to the money kernel + test + ADR doc (2 pts) → Dev Clone\n\n**(a) Files to create / modify (full paths):**\n1. CREATE `src/lib/money/round-to-cents.ts`\n2. CREATE `src/lib/money/round-to-cents.test.ts`\n3. MODIFY `src/lib/money/index.ts` — add a barrel re-export `export { roundToCents } from \"./round-to-cents\";` (place near the existing `./round` export block)\n4. CREATE `docs/adr/0009-round-to-cents-money-primitive.md` — paste the ADR above (Context/Decision/Consequences)\n\n**(b) Expected contract:**\n- Signature: `export function roundToCents(amount: number): number`\n- Pure, side-effect-free, single-purpose (match the co-located lib style + file header-comment convention seen in `round.ts`).\n- Implementation: `return Math.round((amount + Number.EPSILON) * 100) / 100;` (parity with the private helper in `amount.ts`).\n- Header comment must state: half-UP, 2 dp, USD-cents canonicalizer, and the one-line contrast vs `roundMoney` (half-even, aggregates).\n\n**(c) Required test cases** (`node:test` + `node:assert/strict`, mirror `round.test.ts` style — file header with the single-file run command):\n- Normal / already-rounded: `roundToCents(184.22) === 184.22`, `roundToCents(0) === 0`, `roundToCents(1.5) === 1.5`\n- Non-tie rounding: `roundToCents(1.234) === 1.23`, `roundToCents(1.236) === 1.24`\n- Rounding-boundary (half-up tie): `roundToCents(0.005) === 0.01`, `roundToCents(2.675) === 2.68` (note: differs from `roundMoney`'s 2.68-via-even and 0.005→0.00 — pin this to prove the half-up distinction)\n- Negative cases: `roundToCents(-1.234) === -1.23`, `roundToCents(-1.236) === -1.24`, and the negative-tie behavior `roundToCents(-1.005) === -1` (Math.round rounds the .5 tie toward +∞ — assert the actual value to lock the contract; document it in a test comment)\n- Float-safety: `roundToCents(0.1 + 0.2) === 0.3`\n\n**(d) Validation commands (run on YOUR increment; all must pass):**\n- `npx tsx --test ./src/lib/money/round-to-cents.test.ts` (new file alone)\n- `npm test` (full suite globs `src/**/*.test.ts` — confirm no regressions)\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` (typecheck clean)\n- `npm run lint` (lint your changed files clean)\n\n**(e) Scope boundary — DO NOT touch:** `src/features/ledger/lib/amount.ts`, `round.ts`, `arithmetic.ts`, `format.ts`, any `src/app/**` route, any feature module. No refactor of `amount.ts` to consume the new util in this PR. Only the 4 files in (a).\n\n**Flow:** isolate in a worktree off `main`, open a PR via `gh pr create`, emit `dev-clone.pr.created` + `implementation.completed`. QA Guardian is sole merge authority.\n\n**Messages summary:** ADR 0009 (half-up `roundToCents` promoted to the money kernel) · 1 task · 2 points.", "content_type": "success", "priority": "normal"}}

